To find the area of the plot of land in acres, we first need to convert the dimensions from the map scale to actual miles. Since the scale is 1 cm = 2 miles, the dimensions of the plot in miles are: \[
\text{Length} = 15 \text{ cm} \times 2 \text{ miles/cm} = 30 \text{ miles}
\] \[
\text{Width} = 10 \text{ cm} \times 2 \text{ miles/cm} = 20 \text{ miles}
\] Next, we calculate the area of the plot in square miles: \[
\text{Area in square miles} = \text{Length} \times \text{Width} = 30 \text{ miles} \times 20 \text{ miles} = 600 \text{ square miles}
\] Since the area is required in acres and 1 square mile = 640 acres, we convert the area to acres: \[
\text{Area in acres} = 600 \text{ square miles} \times 640 \text{ acres/square mile} = 384000 \text{ acres}
\] </think> <answer> $384000$ acres </answer>

